  "body": "\r\n# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nMedalla default configuration overwrites any custom configuration. Primary effect is a fork-version that cannot be set. For the next Eth2 attacknet I would like to use a different version from Medalla, to avoid cross-over incidents.\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nNot sure about the exact time it stopped working. But as of a week ago, for the previous attacknet, it worked.\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\n```\r\n--verbosity=trace   --chain-config-file=\"config_example.yml\"   --deposit-contract=\"0xb21c33DE1FAb3FA15499c62B59fe0cC3250020d1\"   --contract-deployment-block=\"3144621\"   --custom-genesis-delay=\"123\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nUse `config_example.yml` from here: https://gist.github.com/protolambda/20ffb29e5a3f39405dce611399b1c0e4\r\nMost important difference with mainnet is:\r\n```\r\n# overwritten by medalla\r\nGENESIS_FORK_VERSION: 0x0000b01d\r\n# does not get overwritten (afaik)\r\nNEXT_FORK_VERSION: 0x0000b01d\r\n```\r\n\r\n- The config gets loaded first\r\n- The genesis fork version is set correctly to `0x0000b01d`\r\n- The genesis fork version is overwritten by:\r\n\r\n```go\r\nfunc ConfigureBeaconChain(ctx *cli.Context) {\r\n\t// Using Medalla as the default configuration for now.\r\n\tparams.UseMedallaConfig()\r\n...\r\n}\r\n// MedallaConfig defines the config for the\r\n// medalla testnet.\r\nfunc MedallaConfig() *BeaconChainConfig {\r\n\tcfg := MainnetConfig().Copy()\r\n\tcfg.MinGenesisTime = 1596546000\r\n\tcfg.GenesisForkVersion = []byte{0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x01}  // <--- bad when custom config is already loaded.\r\n\treturn cfg\r\n}\r\n\r\n// UseMedallaConfig sets the main beacon chain\r\n// config for medalla.\r\nfunc UseMedallaConfig() {\r\n\tbeaconConfig = MedallaConfig()\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that the same bug seems like to exist on the validator, slasher, and other startup commands with similar flow.\r\nAlso: configuring the slasher would be really useful for the attacknet. Otherwise we may not release validators as early, or have to rely on custom builds and/or lighthouse slasher prototype.\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\nNo errors, silent wrong behavior. Just deposit signature failures, because of the bad fork version. Deposits worked on Lighthouse and Teku with same configuration.\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n-\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\ncommit dbd2d9a0bb2bf43d40ef156b0aa58e786845bbaf (HEAD -> master, origin/master, origin/HEAD)\r\nDate:   Fri Jul 31 13:46:03 2020 -0700\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?**\r\n\r\n",
